import React from 'react'
  import { MDXTag } from '@mdx-js/tag'
  

export default class MDXContent extends React.Component {
  constructor(props) {
    super(props)
    this.layout = null
  }
  render() {
    const { components, ...props } = this.props

    return <MDXTag
             name="wrapper"
             
             components={components}><MDXTag name="h1" components={components} props={{"id":"cocoa-pods-workshop"}}>{`COCOA PODS WORKSHOP`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="h2" components={components} props={{"id":"pods-1-keywords"}}>{`PODS-1: Keywords`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`To start the project, go to the project folder...`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`pod init
open -a Xcode Podfile`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`Remove the pounds sign that sets the platform.`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`Then under the #Pod for..., you can add your pods!`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`Check cocoapods website for pods.`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`Then, to install the selected pods, type...
pod install`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`Now, we will want to open up the .xcworkspace file!`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="h2" components={components} props={{"id":"pods-2-updating"}}>{`PODS-2: Updating`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`Change the pod file...`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`eg pod 'Hue', '~> 1.1.0' // update to anything up to 1.2 but not above`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`THEN just back in terminal`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`pod update`}</MDXTag>
           </MDXTag>
  }
}
